## Loop contract
- After any change, run: [verification command]. Show the output — evidence,
  not assertions. Work is not done until the check passes.
- If corrected twice on the same issue: stop, record the lesson below, and
  recommend a fresh session with a better prompt.
- Investigation and bulk file reading go to subagents; keep this session's
  context for the plan and decisions.
- Resumability: keep PROGRESS.md current enough that a fresh session could
  resume from it alone. If you hit a usage/token limit, that is NOT "done" —
  leave PROGRESS.md mid-task with the exact next step so the auto-resume runner
  can continue after the limit resets. Print "[DONE_MARKER]" only when every
  item is complete and the check passes.

## End-of-session learning pass
Before finishing any session: (1) append repeatable lessons below as short
imperative rules; (2) delete rules proven unnecessary; (3) update PROGRESS.md
with completed items, failed approaches and why, and the exact next step.

